HEADWORD: Ecboline
<hw>Ec"bo*line</hw> <pr>(?; 104)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'ekbolh`</grk> a throwing out; <grk>'ek</grk> out +
<grk>ba`llein</grk> to throw.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An alkaloid
constituting the active principle of ergot; -- so named from its power
of producing abortion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

